And well... it’s still a Glock. This Gorgeous ALL stainless pistol was built with one tenant in mind: Be The Best, NO Excuses. Many brands that make a competition line use polymer lowers to cut weight in order to increase speed. It also gives your very expensive gun a “cheap” feel to it. The brilliant minds of Sig Sauer Germany KNEW that speed means nothing without accuracy and controllability. That’s why they built this pistol with SOLID stainless construction. No aluminum or polymer lower. The added weight increases the ruggedness and rigidity of the pistol and also reduces recoil so you can place rapid follow up shots on target without the violent recoil of lighter weight pistols. It has a FULLY adjustable trigger allowing you to change the pull weight, trigger placement, as well as creep and reset to fit your specific needs. I have it currently set at 2 POUNDS with No Creep at all and the Shortest Reset possible in a pistol. I’ve had other competition pistols with compensators such as CZ, Zev Glocks, Agency Arms M&Ps. I shoot better with this pistol than most people do with red dots (including myself), my other pistols had red dots. I’ve been able to get under 2” groupings at 25 yards and have been able to hit a 4” steel target consistently at 75 yards. This pistol has practically no recoil at all. It’s like shooting a 22 pistol. I’m a big Sig fan and the new P320 X-Five is trash in comparison. It comes with the original stainless barrel which has 800 rounds through it, and the new threaded barrel has 400 through it. So in total this gun has seen and flawlessly operated 1,200 rounds.
